This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump in the Oval Office. He welcomed the crew and passengers of Southwest Flight 1380, which experienced an engine failure and made an emergency landing in Philadelphia. The President commended the heroic actions of Captain Tammie Jo Shults and First Officer Darren Ellisor, as well as the leadership of Secretary of Transportation Elaine Chao. He expressed condolences to the family of passenger Jennifer Riordan, who tragically lost her life, and thanked the crewmembers who displayed exemplary leadership during the emergency landing. The President also mentioned the bravery of passengers Tim McGinty, Andrew Needum, and Peggy Phillips, who helped in the crisis. He praised the character of the crew and passengers and expressed his desire for peace in relation to potential talks with North Korea. The President also mentioned the possibility of visiting Jerusalem.